---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Learning & Capacity Building" description="The Alliance doesn't just advocate — it acts. Assess & Align, toolkits, shared learning, and the Burke Platform vision for equitable research and practice.">

  <!-- ── Hero ── -->
  <section class="page-hero" aria-labelledby="learning-heading">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="section-label">Learning &amp; Capacity Building</p>
      <h1 id="learning-heading">We demand change. And we&rsquo;re building it.</h1>
      <p class="page-hero-desc">The Alliance doesn&rsquo;t just advocate &mdash; it acts. Members are developing tools, sharing learning, and building capacity across the sector.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Assess & Align ── -->
  <section class="section" id="assess-align" aria-labelledby="assess-heading">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="section-label">Featured Tool</p>
      <h2 id="assess-heading">Assess &amp; Align</h2>

      <div class="card feature-card">
        <span class="feature-badge">In development</span>
        <p class="feature-desc">A tool built by the Alliance to help Black voluntary sector leaders evaluate research requests for equity, collaboration, and cultural sensitivity.</p>
        <p>Born from the manifesto&rsquo;s demand for equitable research practices (<a href="/manifesto#rec-12">Recommendation 12</a>), Assess &amp; Align provides a structured framework for community organisations to assess whether a proposed research partnership genuinely serves their community &mdash; or simply extracts from it.</p>
        <p>The tool helps organisations ask the right questions before committing to research relationships:</p>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>Is the research question shaped by the community it affects?</li>
          <li>Is funding and ownership shared equitably?</li>
          <li>Are findings accessible to participants, not just academics?</li>
          <li>Does the methodology respect cultural context?</li>
          <li>Is there accountability for how findings are used?</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="feature-status">
          <p class="muted small">Launching 2026. Built by Alliance members with lived experience of navigating inequitable research partnerships.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Resources & Toolkits ── -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="resources-heading">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="section-label">Resources &amp; Toolkits</p>
      <h2 id="resources-heading">Practical guides</h2>
      <p>The Alliance is developing downloadable guides for organisations and individuals at every level of the system. These resources translate manifesto recommendations into actionable steps.</p>

      <div class="grid-2 resource-grid">
        <div class="card resource-card">
          <h3>For Black voluntary sector organisations</h3>
          <p>Navigating research partnerships, securing equitable funding, and building organisational resilience.</p>
          <span class="resource-status muted small">Coming soon</span>
        </div>
        <div class="card resource-card">
          <h3>For researchers</h3>
          <p>Doing better &mdash; equitable methodologies, community co-design, power-sharing in research partnerships.</p>
          <span class="resource-status muted small">Coming soon</span>
        </div>
        <div class="card resource-card">
          <h3>For commissioners &amp; funders</h3>
          <p>Embedding equity in commissioning, funding Black-led organisations sustainably, and measuring what matters.</p>
          <span class="resource-status muted small">Coming soon</span>
        </div>
        <div class="card resource-card">
          <h3>For practitioners</h3>
          <p>Implementing manifesto recommendations in clinical and community settings. Anti-racist practice frameworks.</p>
          <span class="resource-status muted small">Coming soon</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Shared Learning ── -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="shared-heading">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="section-label">Shared Learning</p>
      <h2 id="shared-heading">From the Alliance and beyond</h2>
      <p>A space for blog-style posts, workshop summaries, and curated resources from across the sector. The Alliance believes in sharing knowledge openly &mdash; capacity-building starts with access to information.</p>

      <div class="learning-placeholder">
        <p class="muted">Posts and resources will appear here as the Alliance publishes them.</p>
        <p class="muted small">If you have a resource to share, <a href="mailto:BlackMHManifesto@gmail.com">get in touch</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── The Burke Platform Vision ── -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="burke-heading">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="section-label">Looking Ahead</p>
      <h2 id="burke-heading">The Burke Platform</h2>

      <div class="card burke-card">
        <p>Looking ahead, the Alliance is developing <strong>The Burke Platform</strong> &mdash; an AI-powered knowledge platform that will transform how Black civil society organisations access and use research evidence.</p>
        <p>Named after <strong>Dr Aggrey Burke</strong>, a pioneer in transcultural psychiatry in Britain, the platform builds on the <strong>Synergi Collaborative Centre&rsquo;s</strong> legacy of evidence-based work on ethnic inequalities in mental health.</p>
        <p class="burke-vision">The vision: a single place where Black-led organisations can find, understand, and apply the evidence that matters to their communities &mdash; without needing to navigate paywalled journals or decode academic language.</p>
        <p class="muted small">Early development stage. More details to follow.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── CTA ── -->
  <section class="learning-cta" aria-labelledby="cta-heading">
    <div class="container narrow cta-inner">
      <h2 id="cta-heading">Get involved</h2>
      <p>Whether you want to contribute resources, collaborate on tool development, or implement manifesto recommendations in your organisation &mdash; we want to hear from you.</p>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href="/take-action" class="btn btn-primary">Take Action</a>
        <a href="mailto:BlackMHManifesto@gmail.com" class="btn btn-outline cta-btn-outline">Contact the Alliance</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  /* ── Page Hero ── */
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--primary);
    color: #FFFFFF;
    padding: 5rem 0 4rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-hero .section-label {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    color: #FFFFFF;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .page-hero-desc {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* ── Feature card (Assess & Align) ── */
  .feature-card {
    padding: 2rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
    position: relative;
  }

  .feature-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-data);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--primary);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .feature-desc {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--primary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .feature-card p {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .feature-list {
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem 1.25rem;
    list-style: disc;
  }

  .feature-list li {
    padding: 0.35rem 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .feature-status {
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  /* ── Resource cards ── */
  .resource-grid {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .resource-card {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .resource-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .resource-card p {
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .resource-status {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── Learning placeholder ── */
  .learning-placeholder {
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    border: 2px dashed var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .learning-placeholder p:first-child {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* ── Burke card ── */
  .burke-card {
    padding: 2rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--primary);
  }

  .burke-card p {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .burke-vision {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  /* ── CTA ── */
  .learning-cta {
    background: var(--primary);
    color: #FFFFFF;
    padding: 4rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .learning-cta h2 {
    color: #FFFFFF;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .learning-cta p {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    max-width: 550px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .cta-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .cta-btn-outline {
    color: #FFFFFF;
    border-color: #FFFFFF;
  }

  .cta-btn-outline:hover {
    background: #FFFFFF;
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-hero {
      padding: 3.5rem 0 3rem;
    }

    .resource-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
